 that's gonna make me more desirable physically.

528
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,680
 But I'm not just gonna do that.

529
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:26,040
 I'm also going to give another piece of myself

530
00:23:26,040 --> 00:23:28,480
 a way to being socially acceptable.

531
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:30,040
 So now I'm gonna reject some of these friends

532
00:23:30,040 --> 00:23:31,000
 and engage with more of these friends

533
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,480
 because this is what it looks like

534
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:35,920
 for me to be more desirable to my boyfriend, my girlfriend,

535
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,720
 or that guy or girl that I like

536
00:23:37,720 --> 00:23:38,920
 that hasn't yet asked me out

537
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:39,760
 and yet I'm going to continue to do it.

538
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,520
 And then maybe it's not just that.

539
00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:43,240
 Maybe I'm gonna change my behavior.

540
00:23:43,240 --> 00:23:45,400
 I'm gonna make now some compromises in life.

541
00:23:45,400 --> 00:23:48,040
 I'm gonna bend my physical boundaries.

542
00:23:48,040 --> 00:23:50,320
 I'm gonna be willing to go places

543
00:23:50,320 --> 00:23:51,160
 I know I shouldn't do things

544
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:53,880
 I know I shouldn't spend time,

545
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,200
 more time than necessary

546
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,360
 in things that I wish I could take back.

547
00:23:57,360 --> 00:23:58,880
 Like we give ourselves away

548
00:23:58,880 --> 00:24:00,880
 and what happens is we don't,

549
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:05,480
 we don't get rid of our anxiety.

550
00:24:05,480 --> 00:24:08,880
 What we do is we just multiply it.

551
00:24:08,880 --> 00:24:11,920
 Now instead of one thing,

552
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:14,680
 you have multiple things you have to worry about.

553
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,840
 Just as anxiety is described in the Greek,

554
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:22,840
 it's torn you, not just in two, not just in three,

555
00:24:22,840 --> 00:24:27,800
 but maybe into four or five, six, multiple pieces.

556
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:29,360
 This is what we do.

557
00:24:29,360 --> 00:24:34,040
 We suppress, we obsess over our anxiety

558
00:24:34,040 --> 00:24:36,880
 in the hopes that this is how I'm gonna fix it.

559
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,680
 This is how it's gonna get resolved.

560
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:42,600
 You know what Paul's telling us to do?

561
00:24:42,600 --> 00:24:45,720
 Do not suppress, do not obsess, just confess it.

562
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:48,360
 Just confess it.

563
00:24:48,360 --> 00:24:49,600
 Just come to God.

564
00:24:49,600 --> 00:24:50,880
 Like just come talk to him.

565
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:53,560
 His door's open, he's available, he's close by,

566
00:24:53,560 --> 00:24:54,520
 just pray to him.

567
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:58,000
 Just engage with the God of the universe.

568
00:24:58,000 --> 00:24:59,480
 Like I love that he says here,

569
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:01,480
 "Let your requests be made known."

570
00:25:01,480 --> 00:25:03,760
 Like that verb is a passive verb,

571
00:25:03,760 --> 00:25:06,200
 which just means it's not something you're actively doing.

572
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:07,920
 You're not actively requesting of God,

573
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:10,600
 you're instinctively requesting of God,

574
00:25:10,600 --> 00:25:13,360
 which is what we all do whenever times get hard.

575
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:15,440
 We wanna talk to people about it.

576
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:18,360
 Work is tough, I wanna engage with someone about that idea.

577
00:25:18,360 --> 00:25:20,320
 I wanna process it, I need a sounding board.

578
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:23,760
 I need someone to help me process through my venting, right?

579
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:25,600
 Or in a relationship, like I need my girls

580
00:25:25,600 --> 00:25:28,000
 and my guys to help me out, to process through these things.

581
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:29,640
 We want to talk about them.

582
00:25:29,640 --> 00:25:31,920
 That is instinctual.

583
00:25:31,920 --> 00:25:33,960
 You're meant to let it out.

584
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,280
 But here's what Paul's saying.

585
00:25:35,280 --> 00:25:38,280
 You don't just let it out, you lift it up.

586
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:39,920
 You lift it up to God.

587
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:43,000
 You do, you absolutely go and talk to someone about it.

588
00:25:44,360 --> 00:25:47,800
 You talk to him, that's who you talk to.

589
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,240
 He wants to hear from you

590
00:25:49,240 --> 00:25:53,760
 because he is the only one who can truly help you.

591
00:25:53,760 --> 00:25:59,440
 Charles Spurgeon says, "The best style of prayer

592
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:03,040
 is that which cannot be called anything else but a cry."

593
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,800
 The best style of prayer,

594
00:26:04,800 --> 00:26:07,200
 it can't be called anything but a cry.

595
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:08,960
 It is instinctual to pray.

596
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:09,840
 Like we said at the beginning,

597
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:12,800
 it's hardwired into our human nature.

598
00:26:12,800 --> 00:26:14,280
 And what's fascinating is I was thinking

599
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:16,920
 about this idea, if you think about prayer,

600
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:20,000
 the concept of it may have been taught to you

601
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,400
 by someone else, maybe someone like me,

602
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:25,080
 teaching you about this concept of prayer.

603
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:27,520
 But the practice of prayer was likely not taught

604
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:29,040
 to you by anybody.

605
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:33,120
 Like more than likely, times got tough, things got hard.

606
00:26:33,120 --> 00:26:36,960
 And what you did is you just reflexively started talking

607
00:26:36,960 --> 00:26:37,800
 to God about it.

608
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:40,680
 You kicked God, help, please.

609
00:26:40,680 --> 00:26:42,360
 Like what's happening in my work?

610
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:44,040
 What's happening with my family?

611
00:26:44,040 --> 00:26:45,560
 God, I didn't even say that,

612
00:26:45,560 --> 00:26:47,240
 but look at what's happening to my reputation.

613
00:26:47,240 --> 00:26:49,600
 Lord, please, would you help me in this area?

614
00:26:49,600 --> 00:26:52,120
 It's hardwired into you.

615
00:26:52,120 --> 00:26:53,320
 God has put it into you

616
00:26:53,320 --> 00:26:55,240
 because he wants you to engage with him.

617
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:57,600
 Do you see the love of God in that?

618
00:26:57,600 --> 00:27:00,000
 That he said, "Hey, I designed you for me.

619
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,960
 I didn't design you for all these other things.

620
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,560
 You're not supposed to get sidetracked

621
00:27:03,560 --> 00:27:08,240
 and swept off your feet with a myriad of other anxieties,

622
00:27:08,240 --> 00:27:10,200
 concerns, or worries in life.

623
00:27:10,200 --> 00:27:12,760
 No, you're supposed to be fixed upon me."

624
00:27:12,760 --> 00:27:15,720
 All these things that are demanding your attention.

625
00:27:15,720 --> 00:27:18,640
 I'm the only one deserving it.

626
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:22,280
 I'm the only one that deserves your attention.

627
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:24,320
 I'm the only one that can help you in it.

628
00:27:24,320 --> 00:27:26,720
 And I want to, that's the heart of God.

629
00:27:26,720 --> 00:27:30,440
 Like I know for myself, just to get really practical,

630
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:31,480
 like Kylan, how do you even do this?

631
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,320
 When I wake up in the morning,

632
00:27:33,320 --> 00:27:35,280
 I sit down and the first thing I do

633
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:37,680
 is I take an inventory of how I feel.

634
00:27:37,680 --> 00:27:39,220
 Where are my emotions at?

635
00:27:39,220 --> 00:27:40,560
 That's what I wanna know.

636
00:27:40,560 --> 00:27:43,160
 Like, did I get up off the wrong side of the bed?

637
00:27:43,160 --> 00:27:45,480
 Am I nervous about what's coming today?

638
00:27:45,480 --> 00:27:46,680
 Am I in a fight?

639
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:49,320
 Is there conflict in my home between my wife and I?

640
00:27:49,320 --> 00:27:51,560
 Like, how do I feel right now?

641
00:27:51,560 --> 00:27:54,000
 And what I do as I assess my emotions

642
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:56,880
 is I reverse engineer back from them.

643
00:27:56,880 --> 00:28:00,000
 And I try to figure out why I feel that way.

644
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:04,740
 And so often what I find is they're rooted in anxiety.

645
00:28:04,740 --> 00:28:08,760
 I'm nervous, I'm anxious, I'm stressed about something

646
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:11,720
 that is coming for me later in the day.

647
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:16,260
 And so what I do in those moments is two things.

648
00:28:16,260 --> 00:28:21,520
 I admit them to God and I submit them to God.

649
00:28:21,520 --> 00:28:22,720
 I admit them and I submit them.

650
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,840
 God, I admit this is where I'm at, Lord.

651
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:29,960
 I wish this weren't the case, but God, this is the truth.

652
00:28:29,960 --> 00:28:32,680
 And then God, I submit it to you.

653
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:36,020
 I wish I didn't, God.

654
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:42,380
 And yet, Lord, I know, even at my worst, Christ died for me.

655
00:28:42,380 --> 00:28:45,780
 And so I'm loved and accepted

656
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,480
 and you're capable of changing me.

657
00:28:47,480 --> 00:28:49,680
 This is the way that I approach it.

658
00:28:49,680 --> 00:28:53,000
 What I don't do is I don't spiritualize my complaining.

659
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:56,160
 Like, I don't come to the Lord and say,

660
00:28:56,160 --> 00:28:57,720
 "God, I wish you would help me at work

661
00:28:57,720 --> 00:29:00,460
 "because my boss hates me and my coworkers are so critical.

662
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:03,440
 "And God, I never thought I'd still be stuck in this job

663
00:29:03,440 --> 00:29:04,880
 "and I'm never gonna amount to anything.

664
00:29:04,880 --> 00:29:06,280
 "Oh my gosh, I'm never gonna make a difference."

665
00:29:06,280 --> 00:29:07,800
 Like, I don't just start complaining to God.

666
00:29:07,800 --> 00:29:08,640
 That's not what I do.

667
00:29:08,640 --> 00:29:11,480
 That's indulging my anxiety.

668
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:13,880
 That's permitting it.

669
00:29:13,880 --> 00:29:16,920
 And we don't permit it.

670
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:20,520
 We admit it, we submit it, and then we move on.

671
00:29:20,520 --> 00:29:21,880
 And we trust it with him.

672
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:23,340
 We come to the Lord and we say,

673
00:29:23,340 --> 00:29:26,520
 "God, here's what has my heart."

674
00:29:26,520 --> 00:29:30,240
 We spread it on the table.

675
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:33,000
 We trust him with it.

676
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:37,160
 And then we go forward and believe

677
00:29:37,160 --> 00:29:39,360
 that he will work it for our good

678
00:29:39,360 --> 00:29:42,520
 because that's what he's done all along.

679
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:44,400
 And as we do these things,

680
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:46,000
 what we find is what happens in verse seven,

681
00:29:46,000 --> 00:29:49,160
 "And the peace of God, which surpasses all understanding,

682
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:53,120
 "will guard your hearts and your minds in Christ Jesus."

683
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:55,520
 It's interesting.

684
00:29:55,520 --> 00:29:58,000
 This expression, peace of God,

685
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:02,400
 only appears one time in the entire New Testament,

686
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,920
 which is right here, which feels weird, right?

687
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:06,600
 Peace in God.

688
00:30:06,600 --> 00:30:07,600
 They kind of go together.

689
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:08,480
 Wouldn't you expect that to see,

690
00:30:08,480 --> 00:30:10,120
 you would expect to see that somewhere else.

691
00:30:10,120 --> 00:30:11,480
 It's a match made in heaven.

692
00:30:11,480 --> 00:30:13,760
 And yet what you need to know

693
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:17,500
 is that Paul is saying something very specific

694
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:19,600
 about God's peace in this moment.

695
00:30:19,600 --> 00:30:21,560
 You see, what Paul is saying about God's peace

696
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:25,040
 is he's saying this isn't a transactional peace.

697
00:30:25,040 --> 00:30:28,680
 Like this isn't just a quid pro quo relationship

698
00:30:28,680 --> 00:30:31,480
 where God, I give you my anxiety

699
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:34,040
 and you give me your peace.

700
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,440
 That's not how this works.

701
00:30:35,440 --> 00:30:36,480
 It's not a transactional peace.

702
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:38,920
 And it's not even a constitutional peace

703
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,360
 that I have peace with God

704
00:30:40,360 --> 00:30:43,080
 through my justification in Jesus Christ,

705
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:43,920
 though that's true.

706
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:46,640
 But that's not what he's talking about right here.

707
00:30:46,640 --> 00:30:47,760
 What he's talking about

708
00:30:47,760 --> 00:30:51,680
 is he's talking about an existential peace,

709
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:53,360
 an existential peace.

710
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:54,360
 So what does that mean?

711
00:30:54,360 --> 00:30:56,040
 I'll illustrate it to you like this.

712
00:30:56,040 --> 00:30:58,200
 When my wife and I went on a honeymoon,

713
00:30:58,200 --> 00:31:00,060
 we went to an all-inclusive resort.

714
00:31:00,060 --> 00:31:02,240
 This is an aside, not a part of the lesson,

715
00:31:02,240 --> 00:31:03,960
 but I recommend an all-inclusive, man.

716
00:31:03,960 --> 00:31:05,880
 Like you just spent the last several months

717
00:31:05,880 --> 00:31:08,160
 planning the biggest party of your life.

718
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:10,580
 It's nice to go make some indulgent decisions

719
00:31:10,580 --> 00:31:11,880
 with no cost to you whatsoever,

720
00:31:11,880 --> 00:31:14,280
 an impulsive decision, right?

721
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,200
 Not indulgent, impulsive.

722
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:17,640
 Go make an impulsive decision.

723
00:31:17,640 --> 00:31:19,860
 Go to an all-inclusive resort.

724
00:31:19,860 --> 00:31:21,240
 And yet what we did when we were there

725
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:23,800
 is we spent money on one thing.

726
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:24,920
 And the one thing we spent money on

727
00:31:24,920 --> 00:31:27,160
 is we went to the resort spa.

728
00:31:27,160 --> 00:31:29,320
 I had never been to a spa before.

729
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:31,400
 And I don't know that I've been since.

730
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:34,440
 But that experience was unlike anything

731
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,240
 I had ever had before.

732
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:37,860
 It was otherworldly.

733
00:31:37,860 --> 00:31:42,860
 Like we walked into the spa and everything changed.

734
00:31:42,860 --> 00:31:48,320
 Like the music in the air wasn't like

735
00:31:48,320 --> 00:31:50,000
 whatever party music was playing outside.

736
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:53,800
 Instead it was this, it was the sound of raindrops

737
00:31:53,800 --> 00:31:57,120
 and birds chirping, which doesn't sound that enticing.

738
00:31:57,120 --> 00:31:59,040
 And yet it was incredible.

739
00:31:59,040 --> 00:32:01,720
 And like the look of the room,

740
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:06,600
 the room was like just enveloped in this soft white glow.

741
00:32:06,600 --> 00:32:10,920
 And the smell in the air was fresh.

742
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:13,440
 It's like citrus, mint.

743
00:32:13,440 --> 00:32:14,560
 And then the lady at the front desk,

744
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:18,040
 she even spoke in an otherworldly way.

745
00:32:18,040 --> 00:32:20,240
 "Hello, welcome to the spa.

746
00:32:20,240 --> 00:32:22,640
 It is our joy to serve you today.

747
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:25,280
 Would you like one of our complimentary robes?

748
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:26,120
 Sure."

749
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:30,440
 Two men appear in a robe that's in warm blankets.

750
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:31,280
 You know?

751
00:32:31,720 --> 00:32:36,320
 It was like, it was unlike anything I had ever experienced.

752
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:40,960
 That's what happens when you come to the presence of God.

753
00:32:40,960 --> 00:32:41,880
 That's what this is saying,

754
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,480
 that when you give your anxiety over to him,

755
00:32:44,480 --> 00:32:48,720
 you step into his, you step into his peace.

756
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:53,640
 Like you come into his presence,

757
00:32:53,640 --> 00:32:56,840
 an environment that befits him.

758
00:32:56,840 --> 00:33:01,840
 God, by his very nature, is not morally errored in any way.

759
00:33:01,840 --> 00:33:06,400
 Like from God comes no disorder,

760
00:33:06,400 --> 00:33:09,440
 no disruption, no deterioration.

761
00:33:09,440 --> 00:33:15,140
 He is peace-giving, perfect, whole,

762
00:33:15,140 --> 00:33:17,240
 which is in fact what this word means.

763
00:33:17,240 --> 00:33:19,040
 Like the word here for peace,

764
00:33:19,040 --> 00:33:21,160
 it doesn't just mean tranquility or calm,

765
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:23,120
 it means wholeness.

766
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:26,400
 That when you come to God and you find

767
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:32,160
 that he is as unified and complete

768
00:33:32,160 --> 00:33:34,960
 and not disordered, but ordered and perfect

769
00:33:34,960 --> 00:33:36,680
 as you have been told,

770
00:33:36,680 --> 00:33:41,680
 he takes all of these broken and separated

771
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:44,360
 and torn asunder pieces of you,

772
00:33:44,360 --> 00:33:49,360
 and he begins to make them whole together again.

773
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:52,820
 He unites the parts of yourself.

774
00:33:53,180 --> 00:33:54,380
 That you've given away.

775
00:33:54,380 --> 00:33:59,900
 He takes that obsession you have with your performance,

776
00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:03,760
 that suppression you've applied to your addiction,

777
00:34:03,760 --> 00:34:08,180
 that focus you have on your reputation,

778
00:34:08,180 --> 00:34:10,620
 and he blends them back together.

779
00:34:10,620 --> 00:34:13,820
 And he makes you as he himself is,

780
00:34:13,820 --> 00:34:17,660
 whole, not divided,

781
00:34:17,660 --> 00:34:21,180
 but united.

782
00:34:21,180 --> 00:34:24,100
 This is what this verse means.

783
00:34:24,100 --> 00:34:29,100
 The result of prayer is that it doesn't change God.

784
00:34:29,100 --> 00:34:31,980
 Prayer changes you.

785
00:34:31,980 --> 00:34:35,060
 That's why we pray.

786
00:34:35,060 --> 00:34:36,920
 That's why we come to the Lord.

787
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:41,220
 Like what we find is that God is available

788
00:34:41,220 --> 00:34:42,660
 and capable for us.

789
00:34:42,660 --> 00:34:43,700
 He's available.

790
00:34:43,700 --> 00:34:46,660
 He loves you.

